                                                                                                                                Navigation

                                                                                                                                Link

                                                                                                                                Partially stable

                                                                                                                                A link is text that navigates to another location.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog
                                                                                                                                Common Alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Hyperlink, URL


                                                                                                                                Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Anatomy

                                                                                                                                A link is made of text and an underline.


                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                Use a link to allow users to navigate to a new destination or a different section on a page.


                                                                                                                                Use cases

                                                                                                                                • Navigate to another page or website.

                                                                                                                                • Jump or scroll to a new place on this page (anchor links).

                                                                                                                                • Link to emails or phone numbers (can launch an app).


                                                                                                                                Link versus button?

                                                                                                                                There are many, many articles debating the topic. UX movement wrote an article in 2010 with a very polarized but popular view: 

                                                                                                                                Buttons are for actions. Links are for navigation.

                                                                                                                                While Base mostly aligns with this dichotomy, there are many gray areas.

                                                                                                                                The boundary between buttons and links is fuzzy because a button may take users to a new page as it performs an action. As well as many menus and navigation components commonly contain buttons. So the answer depends on the context and the surrounding elements. These guidelines may help the boundary be more clear:

                                                                                                                                Buttons

                                                                                                                                Links

                                                                                                                                • Performs an action, like sending a form, saving, editing

                                                                                                                                • Opens a dialog, modal, or menu, or changes the content on the page

                                                                                                                                • Label text should be concise.

                                                                                                                                  • For example, “Edit"

                                                                                                                                • Common in mobile and web contexts


                                                                                                                                • The link is written as a sentence or as part of a sentence

                                                                                                                                  • For example, “Participation in the Program is subject to these terms and conditions for Renewable Membership."

                                                                                                                                • Redirects to an external site or document

                                                                                                                                • Label text can be longer

                                                                                                                                  • For example, “Uber Cash Purchase Agreement”

                                                                                                                                • Common in web contexts but less common in mobile


                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Do use a button treatment with gray background protection, not a link, to indicate an action.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use a link treatment for actions.
                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Do use a button, instead of a link, for an action like cancelling a task.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use a link treatment for an action like cancelling a task.


                                                                                                                                For accessibility purposes, we must ensure we have the appropriate minimum touch targets in a mobile context for actions we'd like users to take. See also building with minimum touch targets.


                                                                                                                                Links embedded in a sentence

                                                                                                                                Links embedded within sentences can be difficult to translate and challenging for screen reader users to navigate. To make things easier, it may help to place a link or button below a paragraph or link the entire sentence instead of just parts. The order of words in a sentence is specific to the language, so a sentence that works in English and French may not be correct in Chinese or Japanese. Check out global writing guidelines for syntax too.


                                                                                                                                Figma component how-to

                                                                                                                                Figma text styles

                                                                                                                                Any typography style that is a paragraph or label class can be converted into a link by setting the weight to semibold and underlining it.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Do use semibold weight and an underline to style links.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don't use different styles for links. In this example, color differences alone are not sufficient for accessibility. Adding underlines helps users who may not perceive color and those who are less tech-savvy.

                                                                                                                                For designers in Figma, if you're starting with a paragraph style, you will need to detach the type style to achieve this. This is a known limitation in Figma. *Sad cat*

                                                                                                                                Behavior

                                                                                                                                Tapping or clicking on a link navigates to a new location or scrolls to a new place on a page. Links to emails and phone numbers can launch an app.

                                                                                                                                States

                                                                                                                                Enabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and underline: contentPrimary.

                                                                                                                                Hover
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and underline: contentSecondary.

                                                                                                                                Visited
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and underline: contentSecondary.

                                                                                                                                Focus
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and underline: contentSecondary.

                                                                                                                                Focus outline: 2 borderAccent.

                                                                                                                                Disabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and underline: contentStateDisabled﻿.


                                                                                                                                Wrapping and truncation

                                                                                                                                Wrapping
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                A link will wrap onto the next line if it does not fit into its parent container by breaking at the last word that fits on the current line.

                                                                                                                                Hyphenating
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Extra long words that take up more space than their container will hyphenate.


                                                                                                                                Breakpoints

                                                                                                                                For both narrow and wide viewports, the width of the link is usually the same as its text content. The link will hyphenate when it reaches the width of its container.
